<title>MEXICO: Mexico's Autlan announces stock-split offer.</title>
<headline>Mexico's Autlan announces stock-split offer.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexican mining firm Compania Minera Autlan SA de CV said on Thursday it planned to offer shareholders a stock split during a September 10 meeting.</p>
<p>Autlan said in a statement through the Mexican Stock Exchange that it would offer two B shares for each A or B share in circulation. B shares are ordinary shares with voting rights, the company said.</p>
<p>It offered no other details on the proposal.</p>
<p>-- David Luhnow, Mexico City newsroom 525 7289565</p>
